description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to recruit a Team Leader to join the operational management team for Public Health School Health Nursing, Team / Looked After Children’s and Immunisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidate should be a motivated, enthusiastic and dynamic Specialist Community Public Health Nurse – (NMC part 3) with excellent knowledge, skills, experience and proven leadership qualities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will need to provide clinical leadership, direction and encourage development of the teams in order to improve quality and shape services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will support teams to ensure effective implementation of A School Nursing Framework for Wales (2017) , the Healthy Child Wales Programme (0-7) and the requirements for children who are Looked After and school based immunisations programmes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent opportunity for leadership and professional development within a dynamic and forward thinking service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 19th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Victoria Bodger - Senior Nurse Public Health Nursing (School Nursing)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;victoria.bodger@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
